title: Donald Trump sings a poem (The Fat Wall)

json.text: Who has heard the poem called "The Snake"?
[Audience cheering]
So I have it. Does anybody wanna hear it again?
[Audience cheering]
You sure? Are you sure?
[Audience cheering]
Okay. So let's dedicate this to General Kelly, the Border Patrol, and the ICE Agents for doing such an incredible job.
This was written by Al Wilson, long time ago.
And I thought of it having to do with our borders, and people coming in, and we know what we're going to have. We're gonna have problems.
We have to very, very carefully vet, we have to be smart, we have to be vigilant.
So here is "The Snake".
[BEAT DROP]
WE NEED TO BUILD A WALL, WE NEED TO BUILD A WALL, WE NEED TO BUILD A BIG, BEAUTIFUL WALL (x4)

[Trump binging and bonging]
On her way to work one morning
Down the path along the lake

A tender-hearted woman saw a poor half-frozen snake

His pretty colored skin had been all frosted with the dew

[Trump binging and bonging]
"Poor thing," she cried, "I'll take you in and I'll take care of you"
The border.
WE NEED TO BUILD A WALL, WE NEED TO BUILD A WALL, WE NEED TO BUILD A BIG, BEAUTIFUL WALL (x4)

"But if I hadn't brought you in by now, oh heavens, you might have died"

[Trump binging and bonging]

That snake gave her a vicious
